<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1203079>
    dc:description "FIGURE 63. Caligus upeneisp. nov., holotype female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, left corner of genital complex showing fifth leg, ventral; C, antennule; D, antenna; E, post-antennal process; F, maxillule; G, tipof maxilla; H, maxilliped; I, sternal furca. Scale bars:0.5 mm on A, 100 µm on B–H, 50 µm on I." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1203079/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1203081>
    dc:description "FIGURE 64. Caligus upenei sp. nov., holotype female. A, leg 1, ventral; B, leg 2, ventral; C, leg 3, ventral; D, leg 4. Scale bars:100 µm on A, 200 µm on B–D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1203081/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1203061>
    dc:description "FIGURE54.Caligus sclerotinosus Roubal, Armitage& Rohde, 1983, female.A, habitus, dorsal; B, antenna and post-antennal process drawn in situ; C, maxillule and postoral process drawn in situ; D, tip of maxilla; E, sternal furca;F, exopod of leg 2; G, exopod of leg 3; H, leg 4. Scale bars:1.0 mm on A, 200 µmon B,C, H, 50 µm on D, E, 100 µm on F, G." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1203061/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1203067>
    dc:description "FIGURE 57. Caligus sicarius Kabata, 1984, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, fourth pedigerous somite, genital complex and abdomen, ventral;C, left corner of genital complex showing leg 5, ventral; D, antennule; E, antenna,post-antennal process and maxillule drawn in situ; F, maxilliped.Scale bars:500 µm on A, B,100 µm on C–D, 200 µm on E–F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1203067/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1203069>
    dc:description "FIGURE 58. Caligus sicarius Kabata, 1984, female. A, sternal furca and accessory processes, ventral view in situ; B, leg 1, with inset showing setationelements of distal margin; C, leg 2; D, leg 3, ventral; E, exopod of leg 4. Scale bars:200 µm on A– D, 100 µm on E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1203069/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

